  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ 350°F/ Gas 4</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614612263509-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614612263509-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614612263509-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614612263509-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614612263509-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and 10g<span class=\"text-danger\"> [20g]</span> <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>diced carrot</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>star anise</strong> and cook for 6-8 min, or until the onion is starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>black olives</strong> coarsely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614612287543-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614612287543-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614612287543-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614612287543-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614612287543-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> veg stock mix</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>ground turmeric</strong> (save the rest for later!) with 350ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [700ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>turmeric stock</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring continuously, then add the <strong>turmeric stock</strong> and <strong>chopped olives</strong>, and reduce the heat to low</p><p>Cook for 5 min or until reduced by half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614612309227-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
